Ok ... for a "blocker" this has set here too long. 
I'm pretty sure there's nothing we are obviously doing to cause 
this ... just using swt browser ... so, unless someone in community
can help isolate it, develop standalone swt tests?, see if its still 
a problem on M6, etc., I'm tempted to just put in a "hacky" work-around. 
This won't help the browser display, but should prevent the "unable to 
start" part of this problem, which is, of course, the "blocking" nature
of it. 

Any opinons/advice?


		/* https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=87657
		 * used this check for SWTError in attempt to work around 
		 * "blocker" mentioned in 87657
		 */
		try {
			addPreviewPage();
		}
		catch (SWTError e) {
			Logger.logException(e);
		}
